                    <h3 class="content-heading black-color">Custom Suffix</h3>

                    <p>In some cases; using a suffix for naming wonâ€™t be possible. If the suffix does not clearly represent the context of the class, you can create a custom one:</p>

                     <h3 class="content-heading black-color">Guide elements with optional suffix</h3>

                     <p>In the context of some guides; there will be cases where the use of a suffix is not required.
Unordered list (ul) and Ordered list (ol) for instance do not need a suffix. When the use of a suffix does not help emphasize the context of that element, you can omit to use one.</p>

                     <p>
                        <span class="code-description-heading"><b>Example</b></span>
                        <span class="text-code orange-text">
                            ul.navbar{<br/>
                            <span class="indent"></span>li.navbar-item {}<br/>
                            }
                        </span>
                    </p>

                    <p>Note: To avoid class repetition, the custom suffix -item was used here to differentiate the .navbar class for its child element .navbar-item.</p>

